JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura held the annual state of the province address on Monday morning. Speaker of the Gauteng Provincial Legislature Ntombi Mekgwe presided over the official opening of the fourth session of the fifth legislature.Premier Makhura talked of progress on achievements and outline plans on how the current administration will continue to implement the programme for the transformation, modernisation and reindustrialisation of Gauteng.The last year has been a tumultuous one in the province with a number of crisis ranging from school placements for students, Esidimeni tragedy, youth unemployment, housing and other pressing provincial issues.READ: Makhura commits to justice for Esidimeni familieseNCA